{
  "stem": "1975.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "They would have-- they would have never had the opportunity to get out from the Russians.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "If, if, if-- for one stroke of the pen, if he would just not have given me the, the, the-- that used to be called in Russian, [SPEAKING RUSSIAN].",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "That means a transfer.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "I remember that I had to change the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And I crossed over Warsaw through Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And then I joined in the-- I joined in the-- deep in Germany, in the-- about a hundred-- a few hundred miles from Berlin, I joined the-- a a, a new regiment, which was the 132nd regiment from the-- from the-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] [RUSSIAN], which is the-- which is the border patrol.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "I forgot to mention that before that, we went to Ostpreusen, which is Prussia, you know, in the-- and we had taken the-- liberated the city of Konigsberg, which was called-- later changed to Kaliningrad.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "This was before.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "This was when we were in Lithuania and in the vicinity of Latvia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And this was also a remarkable-- a remarkable victory that we had in the-- over the city of-- entering the city of Konigsberg, you know.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "It was an incredible experience for us, and especially for those-- the Jews who were in the camps to be able to see the surrender of a large German Army, whom we had to investigate and, and who were falling in our-- in our hands.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "But now, in the vicinity of Berlin, we came-- in a matter of a few, few weeks, we were transferred-- we were right-- absorbed-- transferred to the Zhukov Army.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "Zhukov was the general who actually liberated Berlin, and who met with Eisenhower at the Elbe at a later date.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
